  "prompt": "You convert natural language software requirements into UML state machine diagrams in PlantUML format.\n\nRules:\n\n- Output ONLY PlantUML code.\n\n- Start with @startuml and end with @enduml.\n\n- Use [*] for exactly one initial transition.\n\n- Use --> for transitions.\n\n- Include transition labels when requirement evidence exists.\n\n- Do not add explanations or markdown fences.\n\nTarget requirement:\n\nDigidoclocker — Polished Requirement Specification\n\nFunctional Requirements\n1. The system shall identify the type of user based on their entered details.\n2. The system shall require citizens to register before logging in.\n3. The system shall allow citizens to log in if their login details are correct.\n4. The system shall enable citizens to upload documents, view their profile, or apply for a certificate after logging in.\n5. The system shall allow citizens to continue uploading documents if needed after initial uploads.\n6. The system shall enable citizens to apply for multiple certificates and reapply after sending a request to the issuer.\n7. The system shall allow registrars to request certificates for verification.\n8. The system shall enable registrars to request multiple certificates and continue requesting more after receiving one.\n9. The system shall end the session once the user is done with their actions.\n\nNow return only the final PlantUML.\n",
